Present course gives an overview of possible methods of neurological physiotherapy assessment, treatment strategies (including different methods, positioning, usage of assistive devices) and counseling in patients with numerous neurological disorders (conditions affecting both peripheral and central nervous system).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide a theoretical overview of the possibilities of physiotherapeutic assessment and intervention in various neurological diseases and to offer the student the opportunity to apply practical skills in the physiotherapy of neurological patients in a real work environment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course student: - Knows the causes of the most common neurological diseases and the physiotherapy methods used - Knows the terminology of neurological physiotherapy - Is able to gather neurological patient's anamnesis  - Can describe neurological physiotherapy assessment methods and use them in practice - Knows basic principles of positioning, mobilization, facilitation, and transitions used with neurological patients - Is able to assess and analyze the development of his/her professional knowledge and practical skills within neurological physiotherapy
